This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the design of activation functions for neural networks. It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it focuses on neural networks. Additionally, since the paper deals with complex-valued data, it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as these fields often deal with complex data. Finally, since the paper proposes a new method for activation functions, it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as this sub-category deals with the design of algorithms for network analysis.
